                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Milledge</persName>, district
                        attorney, to Mr. <persName type="to">Hoar</persName>, Attorney-General.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Macon, Georgia</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-09-03">
                        <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 3, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">To Attorney-General <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoar</hi>:</p>
                <p>Large party of men, thoroughly armed, at Fort Gaines, Georgia, enlisted <pb
                        facs="0830" n="816" xml:id="pg_816"/> for Cuban army. United States deputy
                    marshal finds it impossible to arrest, as the citizens are not sufficiently
                    strong; he telegraphs for troops to assist. General Terry replies that General
                    Halleck will not give the authority. What course shall I pursue? They will get
                    off on special boat to-morrow. Answer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN MILLEDGE,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States District Attorney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
